The Recoverable Dynamic Storage (RDS) package provides an allocator
for RVM segments.  The allocator provides a heap similar to that of
the C library, although with persistence.
Additional provisions for initialization and reloading of the heap
after shutdown or crash are included.
The header file is
included in <ref id="RVMheaders" name="XXX"> on p. @PageRef(rdsh).


